<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-23T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="788" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d788">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/3349: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Sweden (<persName type="from">Greene</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-23T18:00:00+01:00">November
                                    23, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 23—2:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3329. British Minister and I are submitting <hi rend="italic">aides-mémoire</hi> to Swedish Government this afternoon in sense of
                            Department’s 988, November 13, midnight,<note n="62" xml:id="d788fn62">See footnote 61, <ref target="#pg_790">p. 790</ref>.</note> British
                            Minister taking up in addition question of payment of freight and
                            certain details concerning safe conduct including marking of
                            vessels.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Greene</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>